ROTAVIRUS VACCINE RESEARCH: CURRENT STATUS (03)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Rotavirus vaccine research: current status 971124210102
Rotavirus vaccine research: current status (02) 971126224624
Date: Thu, 27 Nov 1997 20:32:14 -0500 (EST)
From: Jim Koopman <jkoopman@sph.umich.edu>

I got the following addendum to my post on rotavirus vaccines:
"[Thanks to Jim Koopman for this information. As we it appears we are
getting far away from our limited area of expertise and cannot sustain such
a discussion here, we are cutting this very interesting and critical
string. - Mod.CHC"
I am disturbed that a major list-serve dealing with the control of
infectious diseases is unwilling to entertain discussions regarding theory
that is needed to understand, evaluate, and predict how different factors
will affect the circulation of infectious agents in populations. The
community that deals with the clinical, molecular and public health aspects
of infection should be using transmission system analysis as one of their
basic scientific tools. They should not be saying that discussions of
transmission system analyses are outside of their expertise. Rather they
should be taking the course I have put on the web and acquiring the
expertise that they need. They will find that this is not so difficult.

--
Jim Koopman MD MPH
Dept. of Epidemiology SPH-1
109 Observatory St.
Ann Arbor, MI 48109
